  "description": "Ground tissue: the tissue system that comprises the bulk of plant organs, filling the space between the [dermal tissue](./dermal-tissue.md) and [vascular tissue](./vascular-tissue.md). The ground tissue system is composed of three cell types, each optimized for different functions: parenchyma, collenchyma, and sclerenchyma.",
